## 4. MCP tool surface (additions)

The existing data tools (design §13.2: `memory_store`, `memory_search`, `memory_get`, `memory_update`, `memory_delete`, `memory_link`, `memory_list`) are unchanged and need **no LLM**. We add tools that make host delegation first-class.

### 4.1 Read-only / deterministic (no LLM, safe to auto-invoke)

| Tool | Returns | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `memory_recall` | Top-k memories for a query, with scores | Convenience wrapper over `memory_search` tuned for agent recall (hybrid + recency/importance). |
| `memory_find_duplicate_candidates` | Clusters of near-duplicate chunks (by vector sim ≥ threshold) | Pure vector math. The *decision* to merge is left to the caller. |
| `memory_suggest_organization` | A **work packet**: untagged items, unlinked entities, dup clusters, episodic clusters ready for summarization | The to-do list the host model walks. No LLM server-side. |
| `memory_stats` | Counts, segments, cache hit-rate, pending-organization queue depth | |

### 4.2 Write tools the host model calls back with its results

| Tool | Side effect | Permission class |
|---|---|---|
| `memory_store` | Insert memory/summary | non-destructive |
| `memory_set_tags` / `memory_update` | Update metadata | non-destructive |
| `memory_link` | Add graph edge `(s,p,o)` from extracted relations | non-destructive |
| `memory_merge` | Merge N memories into 1 (host supplies the merged summary); originals tombstoned | **soft-destructive** → requires confirmation flag |
| `memory_forget` | Soft delete (default) / hard delete (explicit) | **destructive** → never auto; explicit only (design N7) |

### 4.3 The autonomous helper (Tier 2/3 only)

| Tool | Behavior |
|---|---|
| `memory_organize` | If mode is Sampling/Provider, runs the organizer jobs end-to-end server-side and returns a report. If mode is HostDelegated, it **does not call an LLM** — it returns the same work packet as `memory_suggest_organization` plus a hint: "no server-side model; drive this via the agent." |

This makes `memory_organize` safe to expose everywhere: it degrades to delegation instead of failing.

